@10001 = ~Raukner's Ruffian Roughnecks

I've roughed up a militant group of adventurers in Beregost.~
@10002 = ~Raukner's Ruffian Roughnecks

Unfortunately, I could not help the party in Beregost.~
@10003 = ~Raukner's Ruffian Roughnecks

I was able to solve the problem for the group of adventurers.~
@10004 = ~The Quest for Jumper

And lo, it happened that my companions and I set out to find the fluffiest bunny of Faerûn, thy name be Jumper. Westward we must travel as our tasker instructed us and who knows what hazards await us on our journey.

What wouldn't one do for a thousand million pieces of gold. I'm just made for an adventurer's life.~
@10005 = ~A New Best Friend for Ugh

The ogre Ugh has given back Jumper so we could make the girl Kessy happy. Now it's up to me to fulfill my promise and find a substitute rabbit - Kessy has mentioned her father at the Carnival.~
@10006 = ~The Quest for Jumper

We were able to bring Kessy back her favourite rabbit. Now I remember why I like being an adventurer.~
@10007 = ~A New Best Friend for Ugh

Ugh is marching into the big wide world with his rabbit Little-Little-Ugh. A noble endeavor, in my opinion there are not enough big fellows with rodents in the world.~
@10008 = ~Mrs. Brunnstein in Nashkel misses her Son

I agreed to look for Aaron Brunnstein. The boy went for a mountain trip with his fiancée and was never seen again. Perhaps the ranger Barin in the temple in Nashkel can help us.~
@10009 = ~A Ghost in the Cloudpeaks?

Some farmers report to have seen a strange figure at night by the waterfall.~
@10010 = ~The Quest for Perwell

I could not find Perwell in the mines... I hope that he managed to get out with the other slaves before the water broke in.~
@10011 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel?

In the headquarters of the Serpents I've learned some bad news: Their initial plan was, apparently, to capture an ancient dwarven device called Gundmagtor, which translated into common language means something like 'Caller of the black souls'. The main stroke of the cult seems to focus on Nashkel.~
@10012 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Lugosch

Lugosch, the leader of the Serpents of Abbathor from Baldur's Gate, is on site in the Nashkel Mines. There will be no escape for him this time.~
@10013 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Shadowy Dwarves

Apparently we have learned what the use of the Gundmagtor is. It calls forth some kind of shadow warriors who are under the domination of the user. I must conquer or destroy this device.~
@10014 = ~The Serpents of Abbathors in Nashkel - Missing Miners

There still seem to be a few miners in the pit.~
@10015 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Monsters

The Serpents seem to have brought a couple of giant monsters into the mine. That would surely disturb mining.~
@10016 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Emerson's notes

Emerson is missing his notes since the attack of the Serpents of Abbathor.~
@10017 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Monsters

I killed the two Umber Hulks the Serpents have brought into the mine.~
@10018 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Emerson's notes

I was able to find Emerson's notes. He will certainly be pleased to get them back.~
@10019 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor in Nashkel - Missing Miners

I was able to rescue the missing miners from the clutches of a mad cleric. Emerson surely will be happy about the news.~
@10020 = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I could stop the advance of the Serpents in the area of Baldur's Gate, at least I hope so. Lugosch Grayshirt is dead and I have no informations about any other leaders of the cult. But I cannot say why my own name was mentioned so explicitly. Maybe one day I'll find out this secret - whether I like the answer I do not know.~
@10021 = ~A Dead Dwarf and a Message

In Mulahey's cellars I found a dead dwarf who had a message for Mulahey - apparently the receiver was not particularly interested in what the messenger had to say. The message speaks of a meeting in Beregost. Maybe I should go investigate this matter.~
@10022 = ~A Mysterious Dwarf in Beregost

Tarash Blackhelmet was extremely suspicious and aggressive - I had to kill him. Among his possessions there was a letter pointing out that there will be an assassination north of the city...~
@10023 = ~A Mysterious Dwarf in Beregost

Tarash Blackhelmet spoke of the "Serpents of Abbathor" - whoever they might be. And he said that something is going to happen north of Beregost... I should keep an eye on the Crossroads.~
@10024 = ~The Lost Son

We have informed Mrs. Brunnstein that her son is dead.~
@10025 = ~The Lost Son

I found Aaron in the Gnoll Stronghold. He awaits us on the other side of the bridge.~
@10026 = ~A Ghost in the Cloudpeaks

Aaron gave us the solution. Marina had promised not to go to sleep before she would get his engagement ring. I should bring her the ring.~
@10027 = ~A Ghost in the Cloudpeaks

It seems as if everything has been settled. Marina has received the ring and can finally rest in peace.~
@10028 = ~The Quest for Perwell

The elf Aphriel is looking for her son Perwell in the Cloakwood forest. The Bandits have kidnapped him and apparently took him to a secret location.~
@10029 = ~The Quest for Perwell

I've actually found Perwell in the mine and sent him out. On the one hand, I could certainly bring him through the woods... but on the other hand Aphriel could pay me a good ransom for the little one...~
@10030 = ~The Quest for Perwell

I've actually found Perwell in the mine and sent him out. I have no time to mess about with children.~ //"struggle klang so, als wolle der PC mit ihm kämpfen
@10031 = ~The Quest for Perwell

Aphriel is now searching for her son herself. At least I saved him from the mine.~
@10032 = ~The Quest for Perwell

Aphriel and her son are happily reunited.~
@10033 = ~Of Wolves and Men

The husband of the mage Aiwell seems to have been infected with Lycanthropy. I probably have two options to solve the problem: Either with a potion I can get from Thalantyr, or the old fashioned sword solution.~
@10034 = ~Of Wolves and Men

Thalantyr has enumerated several ways. He can mix the potion with Aiwell's blood, which is highly questionable. Or he can use Guril berries that do not always work. The best would be an elixir of belladonna. He also told us that he'll only be able to brew one of the potions.

I could also bring him the corpse of Thonder so that he can better understand the werewolf disease.~
@10035 = ~Of Wolves and Men

Thalantyr has dearly bought the dead body of Thonder in exchange of a Flaming Sword. Not bad either.~
@10036 = ~Of Wolves and Men

Aiwell and Thonder were overjoyed that the man was freed from his curse.~
@20001 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

The halfling lady Emmi Wiesner has downright begged us to look for her son, who was drawn into the clutches of the Cult.~ //"to look after" kenne ich als "sich kümmern um"
@20002 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

I've found Bunger and persuaded him to come with me. He will remain quiet until I have banished the danger posed by the Cult.~
@20003 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

I've found Bunger and persuaded him to flee. However, the cult has been alerted by that.~
@20004 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

I've found Bunger. He was, unfortunately, unapologetic and alerted the rest of the cult. I had to kill him.~
@20005 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

In an attempt to save himself, Bunger Wiesner died under the city.~
@20006 = ~The Cult of the Unseeing Eye - Bunger Wiesner

Bunger Wiesner has returned to his mother. The old lady surely will want to thank us.~
@20023 = ~A Mysterious Offer

A messenger has brought me an invitation from his master. Although he will keep his name secret, he somehow has an interest in me. If I want to get involved in a meeting than I'll meet the messenger in the Copper Coronet.~


