//Karlini Journals
@2000001   = ~The magnificent Karlini - The spellbook of the magnificent Karlini

Inside the Friendly Arm Inn we met a gnome called Ygnatius Bombastus III.
He offered 300 pieces of gold if we receive one of the spellbooks of the magnificent Karlini which could be found inside the Ulcaster Ruins.~

@2000002   = ~The magnificent Karlini - The spellbook of the magnificent Karlini

Luckily we found the spellbook of the magnificent Karlini in the Ulcaster Ruins.~

@2000003   = ~The magnificent Karlini - The spellbook of the magnificent Karlini

We gave Ygnatius the spellbook of the magnificent Karlini as promissed. After some research he found the fitting spell to track down Karlini and we agreed to oversee his task of casting the spell. For that we will meet with Ygnatius at the stone cirlce at Lion's Way.~

@2000004   = ~The magnificent Karlini

We told Ygnatius to not continue working for him.~

@2000005   = ~The magnificent Karlini

We gave Ygnatius the spellbook of the magnificent Karlini and received our reward as promissed.~

@2000006   = ~The magnificent Karlini

We oversaw the casting of the spell but surprisingly a balor appeared and Ygnatius vanished. It was a tough fight to take the balor down but we did it. Unfortunately we don't know of a way to bring Ygnatius back from whereever he is right now.~

@2000007   = ~The magnificent Karlini

We oversaw the casting of the spell but surprisingly a balor appeared and Ygnatius vanished. Unexpectedly the fiend agreed on letting the two gnomes go for my soul in exchange. I refused the offer and the balor vanished into thin air.~

@2000008   = ~The magnificent Karlini

We oversaw the casting of the spell but surprisingly a balor appeared and Ygnatius vanished. Unexpectedly the fiend agreed on letting the two gnomes go if we would answer some difficult questions about the Sword Coast correctly. Otherwise my soul would be his reward. By luck and effort I was able to answer all three questions correctly. In return the balor vanished into thin air but stayed true to his word and brought the two gnomes back save and sound. They in return were thankful - more or less- for their rescue. Gnomes ... In retrospect the delivered reward by theese two gnomes was fitting the needed efforts to solve the given tasks.~

@2000009   = ~The magnificent Karlini~

//Geraldo's Journal entries

@3000001   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate

Travelling through the streets of Baldur's Gate we met a man who referred to himself as 'Geraldo the Magnificent'. He told us he had planned to create blue colour from the fur of gibberlings but when they started to breed uncontrollably he was forced to imprison them in his own house. He asked us to go to his house and deal with the monsters inside. By now there should be around 20 of the little beasts there.~
@3000002   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate

There were only two gibberlings in Geraldo’s house. We should return to him and give him the furs anyway.~
@3000003   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate

Geraldo asked us to find the remaining gibberlings. To make things easier he gave us a bird named Elminster, who will notify us when gibberlings are in the vicinity. To sweeten the deal he will also reward us with 50 pieces of gold for every fur collected, and a useful item should we be able to find all of them.~
@3000004   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate

We were able to find all the remaining gibberlings. When we informed Geraldo he inexplicably left, mumbling something about finding his luck somewhere else.~
@3000005   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate

We told Geraldo that we quit his little task. He mumbled something about finding his luck somewhere else and left.~

@3000006   = ~Breeding Gibberlings in Baldur's Gate~

@3000007  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I witnessed an ambuch at the Coast Way and found a journal from a dwarf named Bashrik. I should bring it to the Temple of Helm in Baldur's Gate.~
 
@3000008  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I agreed to confront this Draglon who was mentioned in Bashrik's journal. As far as I know he might be in the Undercellars.~

@3000009  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I confronted Draglon, but he escaped. I should return to the temple of Helm and talk to the dwarves.~

@3000010  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

A mage named Jenna keeps an artifact for the dwarves. She and her companion Jassir reside in the Northwestern District's tavern. I need to go there and tell her "Greetings from Mirjala" for password.~

@3000011  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I decided to help the dwarves no further.~

@3000012  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

Jenna was killed by the Serpent's minions, and the artefact was taken. I should return to Wostock and tell him about it!~

@3000013  = ~The Serpents of Abbathor

I agreed to have a look at a warehouse in the Southeastern District of Baldur's Gate. We believe this to be the hideout from the Serpents of Abbathor. I will need a key to enter.~